                                            children: "The initial proof of concept was done with 0.5 mM Cholic Acid (CA) and Chenodeoxycholic Acid (CDCA) and 5 nM BRIGHT-V2.1. 10 mM stocks were made for these bile acids, but had to be dissolved in 100% ethanol to guarantee complete dissolution. We initially interpreted the decrease in mNeonGreen intensity (533nm) as a sensor response to bile acid binding. However, upon further analysis, we discovered that this effect was due to the organic solvents used to dissolve some bile acids (ethanol or DMSO). With a relatively weak bile acid stock solution (10 mM) and 100% ethanol, the final concentration of ethanol in the proof of concept assay was 5% (v/v). This caused the protein to denature, reducing the overall bioluminescence output and misleading the interpretation of sensor activity."
