                                children: " The final BRIGHT-V3 design was developed through three iterative engineering cycles, resulting in a highly sensitive bile acid sensor based on a split NanoLuc luciferase system with a DarkBiT/SBiT off–on mechanism. This version eliminates mNeonGreen from the sensor core and instead uses a separate BRET-based calibrator for stable, ratiometric readout. BRIGHT-V3 showed high purity and expression yields after double-tag purification, resolving previous truncation issues that were encountered in BRIGHT-V2. Functionally, it demonstrated strong blue emission increases upon bile acid binding, with affinities aligning with known FXR-ligand binding trends (Kd values in the nM–µM range). Both camera and smartphone assays confirmed clear, quantifiable color changes, with the Samsung Galaxy S10 accurately detecting dose-dependent responses. This establishes BRIGHT-V3 as a viable, equipment-free diagnostic tool for point-of-care bile acid detection."
