                                    label: "Patients are the most direct beneficiaries of BRIGHT, making their perspective indispensable. They include individuals already diagnosed with BAM, those navigating the diagnostic pathway for chronic diarrhea, and patients waiting for answers to unexplained gastrointestinal issues. Their lived experiences provide insight into the day-to-day impact of chronic diarrhea and BAM, highlighting unmet needs, practical challenges, and quality-of-life considerations. By understanding what matters most to patients, we can ensure BRIGHT addresses meaningful outcomes, improves the diagnostic journey, and ultimately provides solutions that make a difference in people’s lives.",
