                className: "english",
                children: "Yes, then I like to go back to my blog that I had about measuring things. And there I measured all kinds of things in my life. I tested all kinds of apps. I measured all kinds of things, but at some point, I remember very well, I was eating with friends and they said to me, Peter, how nice that you measure things, but what do you do with it? What do you get out of it? And around the same time I came into contact with the term biohacking. That was then, I heard that in an American podcast. Then there was also a conference in Finland, the Biohacker Summit. I went there and then I really thought, wow, this is really cool. So there were people who were measuring, that's still an important part of biohacking. And there are also whole gradations in biohacking. So a light form you could say is that you measure sleep. And then you look at, okay, what interventions in my life can I do to optimize my sleep quality? So I stop drinking coffee at twelve o'clock in the afternoon. I don't drink alcohol after four o'clock in the afternoon. I eat, I've also done this, the skin of kiwis, because that helps improve my sleep quality. Or I take certain supplements."
