                className: "english",
                children: "Yes, and that's what the term biohacking is about. Hacking is more about the white hat hackers, the positive hackers so to speak, who actually use the system also for things it wasn't originally intended for. And the idea of biohackers, then we can also hack human biology, by measuring it well, doing an intervention and seeing what the effect of that is. And that's indeed about lifestyle and that kind of thing, but the other extreme is the more extreme hacking of your biology. So those are also people who say, well, we can now do CRISPR-Cas on crops. And on other things, or it's already being used in certain medical experiments. But there are also people in that field who say why couldn't we improve ourselves as humans. So that's one example, modified humans. Another example is brain implants, where people also say can't we also use that to improve humans. So a whole spectrum actually of biohacking, which I still find very fascinating."
