            children: [e.jsx("span", {
                className: "speaker",
                children: "Guest:"
            }), e.jsx("span", {
                className: "english",
                children: "Yes. Because the manufacturer wants... Look, on the other hand, that's how they also solve it. They say, you know, we can also say, we do a kind of subscription. And we treat, that costs you a hundred thousand per year. I'm just saying something, I really have no clue. And if a year later it's still good enough, then you pay another hundred thousand. And that's how we just continue every year. At the end of the song we have our money in. And you as a community are very happy that you haven't transferred a huge amount to the manufacturer. But yes, it's of course... If you're very cynical, the chronic patient is naturally... The most interesting patient for manufacturers. And... Yes, on the other hand, you also compete with other manufacturers. So if you don't bring it to market, there's another one who develops that. And then you with your own clotting factors, you can't get rid of them anymore, because everyone is treated with gene therapy. So there's naturally competition in that. But in terms of business model you'd rather have a fixed steady income. But yes, that's not what we're here for. We want to help and cure people."
            })]
